# Example clipmesh MIME rules file (lives at ~/.config/clipmesh/mimetypes).
#
# One line per type: <mime> <allow|deny> [max-size]
#   - allow/deny: whether that type syncs at all
#   - max-size (optional): per-type cap, on top of max_payload_size (e.g. 4MiB)
#
# clipmesh manages this file for you: it creates it, appends any new type it
# sees using the config's unknown_mime default at the end, and reloads it when
# it changes (so edits apply right away). Your existing lines,
# comments, and ordering are left untouched; a line that doesn't parse is kept
# but commented out.
#
# This is just an illustrative example — yours will be generated from what you
# actually copy. Flip the allow/deny values to taste.
image/png allow
image/jpeg allow
text/html allow
text/plain allow
text/plain;charset=utf-8 allow
# X11/XWayland apps offer text under these uppercase targets:
STRING allow
UTF8_STRING allow
TEXT allow
# A bulky type you'd rather not sync, or want to cap:
image/bmp deny
image/tiff allow 16MiB
